videos.description: Kentucky's Keldon Johnson throws down a dunk, and Auburn's Horace Spencer answers with a powerful dunk of his own.
videos.headline: Auburn & Kentucky go back-to-back with big dunks

videos.description: Charles Barkley jokes with Dick Vitale about not being named a McDonald's All-American: "I ate at McDonald's."
videos.headline: Barkley jokes about not being a McDonald's All-American

videos.description: Bryce Brown sinks a 3 and draws the foul on Kentucky to go to the line for the 4-point play.
videos.headline: Auburn's Brown cashes 4-point play

videos.description: Malik Dunbar flies in to catch the lob pass on the fast break and puts in a fancy reverse layup to keep Auburn's momentum going.
videos.headline: Dunbar catches lob for nice reverse layup

videos.description: Bryce Brown cuts to the basket and throws down a strong two-handed slam.
videos.headline: Brown throws down big slam

videos.description: Auburn's Horace Spencer gets cut badly on his head after landing on the ground hard after absorbing a flagrant 1 foul.
videos.headline: Spencer bleeds from head after hard foul

videos.description: Jared Harper pulls up in the face of Kentucky's defense to sink a 3-pointer to give Auburn the lead late in regulation.
videos.headline: Auburn takes late lead on Harper pull-up 3

videos.description: Kentucky's Immanuel Quickley misses a free throw that would have put Kentucky up by 3, but Auburn can't sink the long 3 to win.
videos.headline: Auburn misses long-distance game-winner

videos.description: Coach John Calipari says he loves his team's defensive play in Kentucky's 82-80 road win against Auburn.
videos.headline: Coach Calipari pleased with team defense vs. Auburn
